"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801054","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-13","<p>The CPS randomly selected 2 case files from each calendar month in 2016 flagged as ‘rape’ on the Case Management System for every CPS area in England and Wales.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-12-13T15:21:08.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801054/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801054/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-05","Rape: Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 November 2017 to Question 9826, what method the CPS used to select the sample of case files to assess the frequency and outcome of applications seeking to introduce into rape proceedings evidence of the complainant's sexual history under s.41 of the Youth Justice and Criminal Evidence Act 1999.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","117613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801055","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-13","<p>The CPS selected case files covering finalised proceedings flagged as ‘rape’ on the Case Management System (CMS). A case will be flagged as ‘rape’ if it is referred to the CPS for a charging decision on one of the following offences:</p><ul><li>S1 Sexual Offences Act 1956</li><li>S5 Sexual Offences Act 1956</li><li>S1 Sexual Offences Act 2003</li><li>S5 Sexual Offences Act 2003</li><li>S30(3) Sexual Offences act 2003</li><li>An attempt to commit any of the above offences under the Criminal Attempts Act 1981</li><li>Incitement or conspiracy to commit any of the above offences</li></ul>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-12-13T15:20:51.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801055/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801055/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-05","Rape: Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 November 2017 to Question 9826, what crimes were selected for the sample of case files selected by the CPS to assess the frequency and outcome of applications seeking to introduce into rape proceedings evidence of the complainant's sexual history.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","117614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801056","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-13","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service selected 309 case files flagged as ‘rape’ on the Case Management System which were finalised in the calendar year 2016.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2017-12-13T15:20:28.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801056/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801056/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-05","Rape: Trials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 13 November 2017 to Question 9826 how many case files were selected by the Crown Prosecution Service for the sample of case files selected to assess the frequency and outcome of applications seeking to introduce into rape proceedings evidence of the complainant's sexual history.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","117615"
