"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800627","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>Consular staff in India were made aware of allegations of mistreatment through Mr Johal's legal representation. Our priority is to inquire about these specific allegations with Mr Johal in private. We take all allegations of torture of mistreatment extremely seriously and we will press for action appropriate to the situation, with the consent of the individual, avoiding any action that may put the individual concerned at risk. The Foreign Secretary raised the case with the Indian Minister of External Affairs on 23 November and Consular officials continue to reiterate our request for a private meeting with Mr Johal with the Indian Government. I have personally raised this with the Indian ​High Commissioner.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-12-12T17:14:15.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800627/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800627/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800627/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Jagtar Singh Johal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the Government of India in the case of the UK citizen Jagtar Singh Johal; what reports his Department has received on the treatment of that person; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Bim Afolami","Hitchin and Harpenden","Bim Afolami","117248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800628","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-07","<p>The Foreign Secretary met Foreign Minister Heraldo Munoz in New York in September 2016. I last met the Foreign Minister at EU-CELAC Foreign Ministers Summit in Santo Domingo in October 2016. We discussed a range of international issues on both occasions.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-12-07T17:09:53.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800628/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800628/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800628/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-04","Chile: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he last met his Chilean counterpart in Chile; and what issues were discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","117249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800629","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-07","<p>The latest available data on the outcome of initial decisions on Disability Living Allowance (DLA) to Personal Independence Payment (PIP) reassessments can be found in the statistical tables released in December 2016 here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576641/pip-official-statistics-dla-to-pip-reassessment-outcomes-october-2016.ods" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/576641/pip-official-statistics-dla-to-pip-reassessment-outcomes-october-2016.ods</a></p><p> </p><p>Table 8A shows a comparison of DLA and PIP level of award for DLA reassessment claimants who were reassessed onto PIP prior to October 31<sup>st</sup> 2016, the latest date for which published data is available. Updated tables containing data to October 31<sup>st</sup> 2017 will be published on December 13<sup>th</sup> 2017.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-07T14:31:58.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800629/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800629/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800629/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-04","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants have been moved from a higher rate mobility component to a lower rate as a result of their transfer from Disability Living Allowance to personal independence payments since such transfers began.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","117250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800630","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-07","<p>The requested information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-07T17:53:08.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800630/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800630/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800630/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","Military Bases: Nurseries and Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) nurseries and (b) primary schools there are on Armed Forces bases in the UK.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","117251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800631","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>The table below shows the total Service Pupil Premium funding allocated to schools by the Department for Education in each financial year from 2011 to 2017.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Service Pupil Premium funding allocated to schools</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number of eligible pupils</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12 [1]</p></td><td><p>£9,014,000</p></td><td><p>45,070</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13 [2]</p></td><td><p>£13,093,000</p></td><td><p>52,370</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14 [3]</p></td><td><p>£17,381,000</p></td><td><p>57,940</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15 [4]</p></td><td><p>£19,317,000</p></td><td><p>64,390</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16 [5]</p></td><td><p>£20,668,700</p></td><td><p>68,896</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17 [6]</p></td><td><p>£22,040,775</p></td><td><p>73,469</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18 [7]</p></td><td><p>£22,580,400</p></td><td><p>75,268</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>It should be noted that the rate of funding increased from £200 per pupil in 2011-12 to £250 per pupil in 2012-13; and then to £300 per pupil in 2013-14 and all subsequent years.</p><p>Eligibility for the Service Pupil Premium has also been extended since the funding was introduced. In 2011-12, only those pupils who were identified in the January 2011 school census as currently being Service children attracted the funding. In subsequent years, pupils have also been eligible for the Service Premium if they were recorded as Service children in any school census since January 2011 but no longer have this status (e.g. because their parent has left the armed forces); or if they are in receipt of a pension under the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme or the War Pensions Scheme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>[1]<a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120109202126/https:/www.education.gov.uk/schools/adminandfinance/financialmanagement/schoolsrevenuefunding/settlement2012pupilpremium/a0075963/pupil-premium-2011-12" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20120109202126/https://www.education.gov.uk/schools/adminandfinance/financialmanagement/schoolsrevenuefunding/settlement2012pupilpremium/a0075963/pupil-premium-2011-12</a></p><p>[2]<a href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140107120523/https:/www.education.gov.uk/schools/adminandfinance/financialmanagement/schoolsrevenuefunding/a00200465/schools-funding-settlement-2012-13" target="_blank">http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140107120523/https://www.education.gov.uk/schools/adminandfinance/financialmanagement/schoolsrevenuefunding/a00200465/schools-funding-settlement-2012-13</a></p><p>[3] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2013-to-2014-final-allocation-tables" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2013-to-2014-final-allocation-tables</a></p><p>[4] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2014-to-2015-final-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2014-to-2015-final-allocations</a></p><p>[5] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2015-to-2016-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-2015-to-2016-allocations</a></p><p>[6] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2016-to-2017</a></p><p>[7] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2017-to-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/pupil-premium-conditions-of-grant-2017-to-2018</a></p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-07T17:53:02.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800631/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800631/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800631/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Service Pupil Premium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much was spent from the public purse on the Service Pupil Premium in each year from 2011 to 2017.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","117252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800632","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>In the financial year 2017-18 there are 10,742 schools which are in receipt of Service Pupil Premium funding – totalling £22,515,000.</p><p>The Department for Education does not publish details of Service Pupil Premium allocations to individual schools, as doing so would risk making those pupils who are eligible for the funding individually identifiable.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-07T17:48:04.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800632/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800632/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800632/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Service Pupil Premium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools are in receipt of the Service Pupil Premium; and how much each such school receives.","false","Biography information for Anna Turley","Redcar","Anna Turley","117253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800633","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-14","<p>The Government has no plans to make such an assessment. Certain classes of fireworks (display fireworks) can only be supplied to a person with specialist knowledge. Experience has shown that the current regulations strike the right balance between the enjoyment of fireworks by the public and restricting the sale of fireworks for public safety reasons.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-14T17:08:05.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800633/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800633/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800633/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Fireworks: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if his Department will make an assessment of the merits of lowering the net explosive content a person can obtain when purchasing fireworks without a licence; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Chris Williamson","Derby North","Chris Williamson","117254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800634","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-11","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>I met with the sector at the steel council in September to discuss the steel sector’s proposition for a sector deal, and met sector representatives again in November. We will continue to engage with industry, as well as with the unions, the devolved nations and other partners as we seek to find a long-term viable solution for the industry.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2017-12-11T14:44:33.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800634/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800634/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800634/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-04","Iron and Steel: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to page 239 of the Industrial Strategy, what progress he has made on the development of a commercially sustainable proposition for the steel sector.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","117255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800635","Department for Education","false","2017-12-07","<p>In October this year, we announced that we will use £5 million to trial evidence-based home learning environment support programmes in the north of England, focusing on early language and literacy. Further details of the process for selecting trial areas and interventions will be available shortly.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-07T17:29:08.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800635/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800635/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800635/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-04","Children: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will provide a breakdown of the £5 million budget allocated to the trial of home learning interventions in the north of England by (a) location and (b) type of intervention.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","117256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-12-07","<p>We recently conducted a pilot to consider whether there are any benefits to recording face-to-face assessments. We are currently considering the findings of this pilot, and will use the evidence gathered to make sure we can continue to improve the assessments process.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-12-07T14:00:33.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800636/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800636/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800636/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-12-04","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans he has to make an assessment of the effectiveness of his Department's pilot for recording face-to-face medical assessments for PIP.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","117257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800637","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-12","<p>I discussed the development of the Combined Joint Expeditionary Force concept with my French counterpart, Mme. Florence Parly, when we met in London on 20 November 2017.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-12T17:59:07.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800637/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800637/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","France: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he last had discussions with his French counterpart on the UK-French Joint Expeditionary Force.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","117258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800638","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-11","<p>We are committed to creating an organisation with the expertise required to reach informed and objective conclusions on trade remedies cases. We will ensure that the TRA is staffed by individuals with the right skills to effectively operate the new system. Our detailed review of the structure and resources of the Australian, American, Canadian, EU and United States systems has informed our decision to recruit investigators with legal, economics or accountancy backgrounds. As with other such appointments, appointments to the TRA will be made in accordance with good governance principles and, where relevant, rules on public appointments.</p><p>The Department for International Trade has engaged with a range of stakeholders including all sorts of businesses, and trade unions, throughout the policy and legislative development process for the trade remedies framework and will continue to do so as it sets up the Trade Remedies Authority.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-12-11T16:41:36.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800638/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800638/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800638/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-04","Trade Remedies Authority: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether appointments made to the Trade Remedies Authority will include representatives from UK manufacturing and trades unions.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","117259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800639","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-12","<p>No Royal Navy Type 45 Destroyers have been under tow since November 2016, except for routine harbour navigation assistance.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-12T15:25:05.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800639/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800639/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800639/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Type 45 destroyers have had to be under tow since November 2016.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","117260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800640","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-13","<p>Every ship involves them entering different readiness levels depending on their programmes and Departmental planning requirements together.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-13T14:53:12.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800640/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800640/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800640/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for how many days all six Daring-class Type 45 destroyers have been berthed together at HMNB Portsmouth during 2017.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","117261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800641","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-12","<p>HMS DIAMOND has returned to Portsmouth after she experienced technical issues en route to the Gulf.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-12T15:25:36.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800641/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800641/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","HMS Diamond","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons HMS Diamond aborted her most recent deployment.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","117262"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800642","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-07","<p>The government has no plans to undertake an assessment of the effect of riparian ownership laws on the number and extent of cases of flooding. There is a common law duty on owners of land to keep watercourses clear of anything that could cause an obstruction, either on their own land or downstream if it is washed away. Land owners have the same responsibilities for the upkeep of a culverted watercourse as if it were an open watercourse.</p><p> </p><p>There are no plans to transfer ownership of culverts to the Environment Agency or local authorities. The Environment Agency, Lead Local Flood Authorities and Internal Drainage Boards have powers to require landowners to maintain the flow of their watercourses.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-12-07T12:11:41.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800642/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800642/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-04","Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if his Department will make an assessment of the effect of riparian ownership laws on the number and extent of cases of flooding; and whether there are plans to transfer ownership of culverts with the potential to cause flooding to (a) the Environment Agency or (b) local authorities.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","117263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800643","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Royal Navy vessels which have fulfilled Operation Kipion responsibilities are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMS ATHERSTONE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS BANGOR</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS BLYTH</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS CHIDDINGFOLD</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS DARING</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS DAUNTLESS</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS DEFENDER</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS DUNCAN</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS ECHO</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS ENTERPRISE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS KENT</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS LEDBURY</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS MIDDLETON</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS MONMOUTH</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS MONTROSE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS NORTHUMBERLAND</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS PENZANCE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS PORTLAND</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS QUORN</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS RAMSEY</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS RICHMOND</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS SHOREHAM</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS SOMERSET</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS ST ALBANS</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HMS WESTMINSTER</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Royal Fleet Auxiliary has also fulfilled Operation Kipion responsibilities. The ships involved were:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>RFA CARDIGAN BAY</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RFA DILIGENCE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RFA FORT AUSTIN</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RFA FORT ROSALIE</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RFA FORT VICTORIA</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>RFA LYME BAY</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-12T17:19:53.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800643/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800643/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-04","Middle East: Peacekeeping Operations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which Royal Navy surface vessels have fulfilled Operation Kipion responsibilities since 2014.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","117264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800644","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-12","<p>Work is currently underway to develop the appropriate methodology for constructing normal value in dumping investigations in cases where domestic prices are inappropriate. Work is also underway examining the options for calculating injury.</p><p>We expect this process to take some months, but we will discuss our thinking with interested parties as it develops and will continue to engage with a range of stakeholders on the detail of trade remedies policy as we have done since the summer.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","117271","2017-12-12T17:59:44.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800644/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800644/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-04","Trade Remedies Authority","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if his Department will bring forward draft (a) legislative proposals or (b) policy papers on how the Trade Remedies Authority will construct normal value in dumping investigations in cases where domestic prices are inappropriate before further consideration by the House of the Taxation (Cross-border Trade) Bill.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","117265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800645","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-12","<p>With cross-party support, the Government has committed £50 million as its contribution to kick-start a society-wide fundraising effort to deliver the National Memorial and Learning Centre and its wider educational objectives. The Government’s commitment has not changed.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-12T17:14:33.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800645/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800645/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to place a limit of £50 million on funding available from the public purse for the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","117266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800646","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-11","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority publishes details of the total hours flown by each individual aircraft, which is collected as part of the process for maintaining the certificate of airworthiness, rather than aggregated by helicopter model. Data for 2017 will be collected at the point each aircraft’s airworthiness review certificate is validated in 2018, so aggregated data by helicopter model will not be available before the end of 2018.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-11T14:40:43.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800646/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800646/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Offshore Industry: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 30 November 2017 to Question 115873, on helicopter flight hours, if he will publish the Civil Aviation Authority’s annual aggregate data for each helicopter model issued with an airworthiness certificate in each year since 2014; and on what the timetable is to publish the aggregate data for 2017.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","117267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800647","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-12","<p>In seeking a prominent location, it was a key objective of the Holocaust Commission for the Memorial and Learning Centre to benefit from existing high footfall in the surrounding area. This is an important part of its mission to preserve the memory of the Holocaust and to raise awareness and understanding of its lessons for the future. The Government’s expectations on visitors to the Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre have been informed by a comparative assessment of visitor numbers to Holocaust memorials around the world.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-12T17:25:02.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800647/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800647/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to his Answer  of 22 November 2017 to Question 111707, what the reasons were for the UK Holocaust Memorial Foundation to envisage that the Memorial and Learning Centre would primarily attract people who already visit the area; and what comparative assessment his Department has made of visitors to holocaust memorials in other countries.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","117268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800648","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-11","<p>The Civil Aviation Authority collects details of the total hours flown by each individual aircraft as part of the process for maintaining the certificate of airworthiness. The table below shows the number of aircraft of each type registered at 31 December of each year, and the total recorded hours flown by those aircraft. The hours flown data has been collected in different ways over time and the total hours flown during a particular year is an averaged amount that has been determined by various methods of calculation, and can be subject to change after data for subsequent years is received.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Type</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Registered aircraft</p></td><td><p>Total hours</p></td><td><p>Registered aircraft</p></td><td><p>Total hours</p></td><td><p>Registered aircraft</p></td><td><p>Total hours</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sikorsky S-92</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>26479</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>32524</p></td><td><p>58</p></td><td><p>40227</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Airbus EC175B</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Agusta AW189</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>330</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>1796</p></td><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>2602</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-11T14:38:13.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800648/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800648/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many flight hours were recorded by the Civil Aviation Authority for helicopter models (a) S92, (b) AH175 and (c) AW189 in (i) 2014, (ii) 2015 and (iii) 2016.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","117269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800649","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-12-12","<p>In September 2016, the UK Government announced that designers and architects were being invited to enter an international design competition for a striking new national Memorial commemorating the Holocaust to be constructed in Victoria Tower Gardens.</p><p>The announcement made clear that competition entrants were also being invited to incorporate designs for a possible accompanying below-ground learning centre, which would be taken forward subject to technical, financial, planning or other constraints.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-12-12T17:24:30.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800649/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800649/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-04","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, for what reasons no public announcement was made of his decision to co-locate the Holocaust Learning Centre with the Memorial in Victoria Tower Gardens.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","117270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800650","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-12","<p>Work is currently underway to develop the appropriate methodology for constructing normal value in dumping investigations in cases where domestic prices are inappropriate. Work is also underway examining the options for calculating injury.</p><p>We expect this process to take some months, but we will discuss our thinking with interested parties as it develops and will continue to engage with a range of stakeholders on the detail of trade remedies policy as we have done since the summer.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","117265","2017-12-12T17:59:44.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800650/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800650/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-04","Trade Remedies Authority","1","House of Commons","To the Secretary of State for International Trade, if his Department will bring forward draft (a) legislative proposals and (b) policy papers on how the Trade Remedies Authority will calculate injury in trade remedy investigations before further consideration by the House of the Taxation (Cross-border Trade) Bill.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","117271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800651","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-11","<p>Aircraft are issued with a non-expiring Certificate of Airworthiness which is validated each year by an Airworthiness Review Certificate (ARC). The table below shows the number of ARCs validated each year for each aircraft type.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Type</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sikorsky S-92</p></td><td><p>42</p></td><td><p>52</p></td><td><p>62</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Airbus Helicopters EC175B</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Agusta AW189</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-12-11T14:31:58.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800651/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800651/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-04","Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) S92, (b) AH175 and (c) AW189 helicopter models were issued with airworthiness certificates by the Civil Aviation Authority in (i) 2014, (ii) 2015 and (iii) 2016.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","117272"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800652","Department for International Trade","false","2017-12-12","<p>Under the WTO Anti-Dumping and Anti-Subsidy Agreements, trade remedy measures can only remain in force for as long as is necessary to counteract the dumping or subsidy which is causing injury. There is no ordinary duration for measures to be in force. The maximum period measures can remain in force is five years.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-12-12T15:34:35.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800652/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800652/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-04","Trade Remedies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether the ordinary duration of trade remedy measures will be five years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Snell","Stoke-on-Trent Central","Gareth Snell","117273"
